Because people don't realize that you send people mid because it's the shortest solo lane, because it's the easiest lane to roam from, and because it's the hardest lane to gank.
You send people there so they can soak up gold and experience and safely transition to lategame. 
{{champion:30}} {{champion:3}} {{champion:268}} 
OR
You send people there so they can get an early gold and exp lead and then start roaming and snowballing the other lanes.
{{champion:4}} {{champion:103}} {{champion:55}} 
OR
You send people there so they can shut down one of the above strategies. 
{{champion:91}} {{champion:38}} {{champion:80}} 

There is nothing about midlane that makes it specifically favor ranged champions who build AP and deal magic damage. It tends to be the mage lane because mages tend to fit one of those three categories, but not every mage can mid and not every mid is a mage.
